House Resolution 94
By: Representatives Stephens of the 164th, Gilliard of the 162nd, and Franklin of the 160th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 2, 2025, as Georgia Arts Day in Georgia; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, arts and culture embody the accumulated wisdom, intellect, and imagination of
3 humankind; and
4 WHEREAS, Georgians recognize the arts and culture industry as a vital pillar of society and
5 a source of pride in their neighborhoods and communities; and
6 WHEREAS, through organizational spending and the resulting economic impact, the arts and
7 culture industry generated $1.3 billion in 2022, supporting 19,734 jobs across Georgia; and
8 WHEREAS, an overwhelming number of visitors to Georgia cite attending performances,
9 events, exhibits, venues, and arts and culture-related facilities as their primary reason for
10 visiting; and
11 WHEREAS, arts and culture play a unique role in the lives of families and communities
12 throughout Georgia, serving as a catalyst for economic impact, stimulating business
13 development, spurring urban renewal, attracting tourists and residents to community
14 activities, and improving the overall quality of life in Georgia communities; and
